rComments: He takes the time to explain everything in as much detail as possible and makes sure, you as students, understand the content. He is quite clear and does his best to make the lecture as entertaining as possible. I highly recommend to go to all of the lectures for the iclicker points and because the lectures really help in understanding the content.

PHYS 212 is quite a step up in difficulty from PHYS 211 (I got a B in this class and a A in 211), so as you can imagine, effective teaching is critical. For the most part, I feel like Seppe Kuehn did a good job teaching-or I should say, applying the concepts from the prelectures. Class is structured similar to PHYS 211, so except lots of homework.
